{"sections":{"main":{"type":"main-page","disabled":true,"settings":{"padding_top":28,"padding_bottom":28,"alignment_title":"left"}},"e2b7edc1-d652-4618-b007-0003c3d77ed7":{"type":"hero-section-3","blocks":{"template--15291250016349__e2b7edc1-d652-4618-b007-0003c3d77ed7-16651460428fa33091-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Gas-X","heading_size":"medium","show_line":false}},"template--15291250016349__e2b7edc1-d652-4618-b007-0003c3d77ed7-16651460428fa33091-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"The drug called Gas-X is used to treat bloating, discomfort, and pain brought on by too much gas in the intestines and stomach. In order to facilitate their easier passage through your system, gas bubbles in your stomach are broken down by Gas-X. This article is meant to provide information to Welzo users so they can better understand gas-x."}},"3697b572-00b3-4873-aadb-01e85df03254":{"type":"button","settings":{"button_label":"Overview","button_link":""}},"c39256d7-f8c0-462f-9109-cc5c53138458":{"type":"button","settings":{"button_label":"Uses","button_link":""}},"e1738aef-38ac-4846-bb48-4dbbbbed5d87":{"type":"button","settings":{"button_label":"Side Effects","button_link":""}},"02803003-6821-40cf-95ac-12d635aeedde":{"type":"button","settings":{"button_label":"Medication","button_link":""}},"6dd2932b-340e-4452-9c4a-96e1a9b89318":{"type":"button","settings":{"button_label":"Ingredients","button_link":""}},"7cfda700-4c13-4a17-9f5a-f70032e2217f":{"type":"button","settings":{"button_label":"Supplements","button_link":""}},"9507a9fe-9b42-4083-bc48-a0a94b4ace7a":{"type":"button","settings":{"button_label":"Pharmacokinetics","button_link":""}},"template--15291250016349__e2b7edc1-d652-4618-b007-0003c3d77ed7-16651460428fa33091-3":{"type":"image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/image-352-1024x1024.png"}}},"block_order":["template--15291250016349__e2b7edc1-d652-4618-b007-0003c3d77ed7-16651460428fa33091-0","template--15291250016349__e2b7edc1-d652-4618-b007-0003c3d77ed7-16651460428fa33091-1","3697b572-00b3-4873-aadb-01e85df03254","c39256d7-f8c0-462f-9109-cc5c53138458","e1738aef-38ac-4846-bb48-4dbbbbed5d87","02803003-6821-40cf-95ac-12d635aeedde","6dd2932b-340e-4452-9c4a-96e1a9b89318","7cfda700-4c13-4a17-9f5a-f70032e2217f","9507a9fe-9b42-4083-bc48-a0a94b4ace7a","template--15291250016349__e2b7edc1-d652-4618-b007-0003c3d77ed7-16651460428fa33091-3"],"settings":{"body_text":"#12022f","padding_top":36,"padding_bottom":150}},"5cbe206a-8974-430b-ab53-0d3a9890d088":{"type":"simple_text","blocks":{"template--15389620011101__5cbe206a-8974-430b-ab53-0d3a9890d088-1673004137a8fb07c4-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"How do I take Gas-X?"}},"template--15389620011101__5cbe206a-8974-430b-ab53-0d3a9890d088-1673004137a8fb07c4-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>Gas-X is available as liquids, chewable tablets, and capsules. The suggested dosage is based on how severe your symptoms are. Take 1 or 2 tablets as needed after meals and before going to bed for mild gas relief. Take three or four tablets, up to four times daily, for more intense gas relief.<br\/><\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15389620011101__5cbe206a-8974-430b-ab53-0d3a9890d088-1673004137a8fb07c4-0","template--15389620011101__5cbe206a-8974-430b-ab53-0d3a9890d088-1673004137a8fb07c4-1"],"settings":{"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"c23c9903-1d44-4abb-905d-51478af2e3ea":{"type":"simple_text","blocks":{"template--15389620011101__c23c9903-1d44-4abb-905d-51478af2e3ea-1673004153f6a3b721-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"What are the side effects of Gas-X?"}},"template--15389620011101__c23c9903-1d44-4abb-905d-51478af2e3ea-1673004153f6a3b721-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>When you experience gas symptoms, such as bloating, discomfort, or pain, you should take Gas-X as needed.Avoid exceeding the recommended dosage because doing so could have negative side effects.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15389620011101__c23c9903-1d44-4abb-905d-51478af2e3ea-1673004153f6a3b721-0","template--15389620011101__c23c9903-1d44-4abb-905d-51478af2e3ea-1673004153f6a3b721-1"],"settings":{"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"72bfe1fd-a8af-4b9c-87e0-49c91e03bfdc":{"type":"simple_text","blocks":{"template--15389620011101__72bfe1fd-a8af-4b9c-87e0-49c91e03bfdc-1673004153f6a3b721-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"When should I take Gas-X?"}},"template--15389620011101__72bfe1fd-a8af-4b9c-87e0-49c91e03bfdc-1673004153f6a3b721-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>When you experience bloating, pain, or other gastric symptoms, you should take Gas-X as needed.Do not exceed the recommended dosage as this may have negative side effects.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15389620011101__72bfe1fd-a8af-4b9c-87e0-49c91e03bfdc-1673004153f6a3b721-0","template--15389620011101__72bfe1fd-a8af-4b9c-87e0-49c91e03bfdc-1673004153f6a3b721-1"],"settings":{"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"6f8de598-5300-44af-a06b-04ebf8522782":{"type":"simple_text","blocks":{"template--15389620011101__6f8de598-5300-44af-a06b-04ebf8522782-1673004153f6a3b721-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Is Gas-X safe for long-term use?"}},"template--15389620011101__6f8de598-5300-44af-a06b-04ebf8522782-1673004153f6a3b721-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>Yes, it is safe for long-term use. If you find that you need to take Gas-X on a regular basis, talk to your doctor about other options that may be available to you.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15389620011101__6f8de598-5300-44af-a06b-04ebf8522782-1673004153f6a3b721-0","template--15389620011101__6f8de598-5300-44af-a06b-04ebf8522782-1673004153f6a3b721-1"],"settings":{"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"93eb9989-e47c-4d6c-80f4-177eca3c1cf1":{"type":"simple_text","blocks":{"template--15389620011101__93eb9989-e47c-4d6c-80f4-177eca3c1cf1-1673004153f6a3b721-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Pharmacokinetics"}},"template--15389620011101__93eb9989-e47c-4d6c-80f4-177eca3c1cf1-1673004153f6a3b721-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>Gas-X is quickly absorbed from the digestive system and begins to work within minutes. Within a couple of hours, the effect peaks. Gas-X is excreted unchanged in the urine because it is not metabolized.<br\/><\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15389620011101__93eb9989-e47c-4d6c-80f4-177eca3c1cf1-1673004153f6a3b721-0","template--15389620011101__93eb9989-e47c-4d6c-80f4-177eca3c1cf1-1673004153f6a3b721-1"],"settings":{"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"deec9f67-3c4c-4291-b9e7-8e124ceea98f":{"type":"simple_text","blocks":{"a5d98b30-71f9-4aa9-80cc-882625fcf965":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Alternatives"}},"2654de7c-0d6e-43bb-a726-dfea75bb4388":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>There are many over-the-counter and prescription medications available to treat gas and bloating. Some of the most common include simethicone, loperamide, and peppermint oil. Talk to your doctor about which medication is right for you.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["a5d98b30-71f9-4aa9-80cc-882625fcf965","2654de7c-0d6e-43bb-a726-dfea75bb4388"],"settings":{"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"a3486db0-039e-4749-aad4-3db832a112be":{"type":"simple_text","blocks":{"template--15389837918301__a3486db0-039e-4749-aad4-3db832a112be-1673021170989925f1-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Overdosage"}},"template--15389837918301__a3486db0-039e-4749-aad4-3db832a112be-1673021170989925f1-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>There haven't been any reports of Gas-X overdoses. However, some of the above-mentioned side effects could occur if you take too much Gas-X. Call your doctor or a poison control center as soon as possible if you believe you have taken too much Gas-X.<br\/><\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15389837918301__a3486db0-039e-4749-aad4-3db832a112be-1673021170989925f1-0","template--15389837918301__a3486db0-039e-4749-aad4-3db832a112be-1673021170989925f1-1"],"settings":{"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"d114524b-ba29-4d5b-bde1-b2c6a8dd69ed":{"type":"simple_text","blocks":{"d6964edb-4706-48da-b349-c4a54ea207be":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"How do I store Gas-X?"}},"55708e90-ccfc-42b6-b479-aaa71f5f397e":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>Gas-X should be kept in a dark, dry place at room temperature.Don't let the Gas-X freeze.Keep pets and children away from Gas-X at all times.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["d6964edb-4706-48da-b349-c4a54ea207be","55708e90-ccfc-42b6-b479-aaa71f5f397e"],"settings":{"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}}},"order":["main","e2b7edc1-d652-4618-b007-0003c3d77ed7","5cbe206a-8974-430b-ab53-0d3a9890d088","c23c9903-1d44-4abb-905d-51478af2e3ea","72bfe1fd-a8af-4b9c-87e0-49c91e03bfdc","6f8de598-5300-44af-a06b-04ebf8522782","93eb9989-e47c-4d6c-80f4-177eca3c1cf1","deec9f67-3c4c-4291-b9e7-8e124ceea98f","a3486db0-039e-4749-aad4-3db832a112be","d114524b-ba29-4d5b-bde1-b2c6a8dd69ed"]}